<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1511,2042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">
Since the new species extremely resembles 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Huang &amp; Zhan" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[689,841,1584,1609]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiaoqingae">
<emphasis box="[689,841,1584,1609]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">P. xiaoqingae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[857,980,1583,1610]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–13" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1483,1508]" captionTargetBox="[155,1427,525,1460]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1435,517,1464]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2–13. Adults of Pedesta wangi sp. nov. and P. xiaoqingae. 2–5. P. wangi sp. nov., male. 2. holotype; 3–5. paratypes. 6–10. P. xiaoqingae, male. 6, 7. from Jiangxi; 8. from Hunan; 9, 10. from Guangxi. 11–13. P. xiaoqingae, female, from Hainan. Scale bar = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3548620" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3548620/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">Figs. 6–10</figureCitation>
), and the latter has been described in detail by 
<bibRefCitation author="Huang, H. &amp; Zhan, C. H." box="[229,482,1619,1646]" pageId="2" pageNumber="358" pagination="179 - 186" refId="ref3130" refString="Huang, H. &amp; Zhan, C. H. (2004) Notes on the genera Thoressa and Pedesta, with description of a new species from south China. Neue Entomologische Nachrichten, 57, 179 - 186." type="journal article" year="2004">Huang &amp; Zhan (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, a comparative diagnosis of the two species are provided as follows instead of a pure description of the new one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1511,2042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">
1. On the forewing of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Huang &amp; Zhan" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[448,600,1692,1717]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiaoqingae">
<emphasis box="[448,600,1692,1717]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">P. xiaoqingae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the upper cell spot is absent or very minute on the dorsal side and present but minute on the ventral side, whereas it is always absent on both sides in the 
<typeStatus box="[1034,1082,1728,1754]" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Xue &amp; Li &amp; Zhu &amp; Lu &amp; Li &amp; Zheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[1243,1338,1728,1753]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wangi">
<emphasis box="[1243,1338,1728,1753]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">P. wangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1511,2042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">
2. On the ventral side of the hindwing, there are well developed or reduced markings in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Huang &amp; Zhan" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[1186,1338,1764,1789]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiaoqingae">
<emphasis box="[1186,1338,1764,1789]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">P. xiaoqingae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but it is totally unmarked in the new species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1511,2042]" box="[199,1435,1835,1862]" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">
3. Cilia on both the forewing and the hindwing of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Huang &amp; Zhan" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[761,913,1836,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiaoqingae">
<emphasis box="[761,913,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">P. xiaoqingae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is checkered, but it is unicolorous in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Xue &amp; Li &amp; Zhu &amp; Lu &amp; Li &amp; Zheng" authorityYear="2019" box="[1332,1428,1836,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wangi">
<emphasis box="[1332,1428,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">P. wangi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1511,2042]" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">
4. In the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Huang &amp; Zhan" baseAuthorityYear="2004" box="[490,641,1872,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Pedesta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="358" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xiaoqingae">
<emphasis box="[490,641,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">P. xiaoqingae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[656,738,1871,1897]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1321,1346]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,306,1294]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,301,1301]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia of Pedesta xiaoqingae. A–H. specimen 1. A. ring, lateral view; B. genital capsule (with the ring removed), right side; C. ditto, left side; D. ditto, dorsal view; E. uncus and gnathos, dorsal view; F. ditto, ventral view; G. aedea- gus, dorsal view; H. ditto, lateral view. I–K. genital capsule of specimen 2. I. dorsal view; J, K. anterior view. L. genital capsule of specimen 3, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3548622" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3548622/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[749,779,1871,1898]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="5.[151,250,853,878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,176,808]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,166,812]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 15. Male genitalia of Pedesta xiaoqingae from Jinxiu, Guangxi. A. ring, lateral view; B. uncus and gnathos, dorsal view; C. ditto, ventral view; D. right valva, outer side; E. left valva, outer side; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. ditto, dorsal view; H. genital capsule (with the ring removed), dorsal view; I. genital capsule, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3548624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3548624/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">15</figureCitation>
), the tip of the left footstalk is shallowly bifurcate (
<figureCitation box="[1349,1432,1871,1897]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1321,1346]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,306,1294]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,301,1301]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia of Pedesta xiaoqingae. A–H. specimen 1. A. ring, lateral view; B. genital capsule (with the ring removed), right side; C. ditto, left side; D. ditto, dorsal view; E. uncus and gnathos, dorsal view; F. ditto, ventral view; G. aedea- gus, dorsal view; H. ditto, lateral view. I–K. genital capsule of specimen 2. I. dorsal view; J, K. anterior view. L. genital capsule of specimen 3, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3548622" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3548622/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
: K, L, 
<figureCitation box="[219,303,1907,1934]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="5.[151,250,853,878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,176,808]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,166,812]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 15. Male genitalia of Pedesta xiaoqingae from Jinxiu, Guangxi. A. ring, lateral view; B. uncus and gnathos, dorsal view; C. ditto, ventral view; D. right valva, outer side; E. left valva, outer side; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. ditto, dorsal view; H. genital capsule (with the ring removed), dorsal view; I. genital capsule, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3548624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3548624/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
: H) or truncate with serrate margin (
<figureCitation box="[718,803,1907,1933]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1321,1346]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,306,1294]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,301,1301]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia of Pedesta xiaoqingae. A–H. specimen 1. A. ring, lateral view; B. genital capsule (with the ring removed), right side; C. ditto, left side; D. ditto, dorsal view; E. uncus and gnathos, dorsal view; F. ditto, ventral view; G. aedea- gus, dorsal view; H. ditto, lateral view. I–K. genital capsule of specimen 2. I. dorsal view; J, K. anterior view. L. genital capsule of specimen 3, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3548622" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3548622/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
: D); the tip of the right footstalk is wide and apparently bifurcate (
<figureCitation box="[265,349,1943,1969]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1321,1346]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,306,1294]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,301,1301]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male genitalia of Pedesta xiaoqingae. A–H. specimen 1. A. ring, lateral view; B. genital capsule (with the ring removed), right side; C. ditto, left side; D. ditto, dorsal view; E. uncus and gnathos, dorsal view; F. ditto, ventral view; G. aedea- gus, dorsal view; H. ditto, lateral view. I–K. genital capsule of specimen 2. I. dorsal view; J, K. anterior view. L. genital capsule of specimen 3, anterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3548622" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3548622/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
: D, J, L, 
<figureCitation box="[446,529,1943,1970]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="5.[151,250,853,878]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,176,808]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,166,812]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 15. Male genitalia of Pedesta xiaoqingae from Jinxiu, Guangxi. A. ring, lateral view; B. uncus and gnathos, dorsal view; C. ditto, ventral view; D. right valva, outer side; E. left valva, outer side; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. ditto, dorsal view; H. genital capsule (with the ring removed), dorsal view; I. genital capsule, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3548624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3548624/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
: H). While in the new species (
<figureCitation box="[872,954,1943,1970]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[241,1351,977,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[230,1358,964,1791]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 16. Male genitalia of Pedesta wangi sp. nov. A–K. paratype 1. A. ring, lateral view; B. uncus and gnathos, dorsal view; C. ditto, ventral view; D. genital capsule (with the ring removed), right side; E. ditto, left side; F, G. ditto, oblique dorsal view; H. ditto, ventral view; I. aedeagus, dorsal view; K. ditto, lateral view; J. juxta; L. genital capsule (with the ring removed) of paratype 2, dorsal view; M. left and right valva of paratype 3, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3548626" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3548626/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
), the left footstalk is triangular and its tip is sharply pointed (
<figureCitation box="[337,421,1979,2005]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[241,1351,977,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[230,1358,964,1791]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 16. Male genitalia of Pedesta wangi sp. nov. A–K. paratype 1. A. ring, lateral view; B. uncus and gnathos, dorsal view; C. ditto, ventral view; D. genital capsule (with the ring removed), right side; E. ditto, left side; F, G. ditto, oblique dorsal view; H. ditto, ventral view; I. aedeagus, dorsal view; K. ditto, lateral view; J. juxta; L. genital capsule (with the ring removed) of paratype 2, dorsal view; M. left and right valva of paratype 3, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3548626" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3548626/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
: G, L, M); the tip of the right footstalk is triangular, with serrate margin (
<figureCitation box="[1222,1305,1979,2005]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1810,1835]" captionTargetBox="[241,1351,977,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[230,1358,964,1791]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 16. Male genitalia of Pedesta wangi sp. nov. A–K. paratype 1. A. ring, lateral view; B. uncus and gnathos, dorsal view; C. ditto, ventral view; D. genital capsule (with the ring removed), right side; E. ditto, left side; F, G. ditto, oblique dorsal view; H. ditto, ventral view; I. aedeagus, dorsal view; K. ditto, lateral view; J. juxta; L. genital capsule (with the ring removed) of paratype 2, dorsal view; M. left and right valva of paratype 3, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3548626" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3548626/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="358">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
